f=Brand Studio/pixel/custom/image-style-guide/SKILL.md · in=image-style-guide translates brand's visual identity **reusable generation parameters**: prompt templates, palette/lighting/composition constants, reject rules. Atlas's kit (§5 Imagery) says what brand's imagery *is*; skill turns what pixel *types generator* batch starts same, operator-approved style DNA instead re-improvising run. · p=gap between "our imagery warm, editorial, people-first" (kit language) prompt reliably produces visual drift lives. skill closes once brand: derive parameters kit, get operator's sign-off test set, freeze them templates amended deliberately, never per-deadline. · wu=Triggers: "image style," "on-brand image," "set our image templates," automatically inside asset-pipeline Phase (every generation pulls brand's templates). · st:/ Protocol=`Derive style params from the brand kit's imagery section (+ real reference images if supplied) \· -> Draft the template file: prompt constants, per-use-case templates, reject rules \· -> Test set: generate 3–5 assets, operator reviews → corrections encoded (like lena's voice loop) \· -> Freeze as the brand's image-style file; asset-pipeline consumes it every run \· -> Rejects at QA cite the specific param violated; repeated rejects → template or kit review` · h3:Phase 1 — Derive=kit's imagery direction (photography style, color treatment, composition, rejected aesthetics) plus any real reference images operator supplies, draft template file `assets/image-style-template.md`: style constants (treatment, lighting, palette anchors tokens, composition defaults), per-use-case prompt templates (product people abstract environment content-image patterns, parameterized), reject rules written checkable statements ("off-palette beyond kit's tokens," "stock-photo aesthetic," whatever kit bans). · h3:Phase Test Encode Corrections=Generate small test set across use cases; operator marks keepers rejects reasons. Corrections get encoded templates operator-correction loop builds lena's voice guide. template ships theory alone. · h3:Phase Freeze Consume=approved file brand's image-style law: asset-pipeline pulls run; deviations rejects citing parameter. Amendments operator-approved versioned (drift "just once" prompts exactly what skill prevents). · of=Phase 1–2 output draft/approved template file. production, skill's output *prompt block* shot: template used, filled parameters, reject rules step check. · pr=**Derived kit, approved real outputs.** Never genre defaults; never frozen without test loop., **Templates law until amended.** Per-deadline prompt improvisation drift., **Reject rules checkable statements.** "Doesn't feel right" reject rule., **Repeated rejects mean template (or kit) needs review** routed atlas/spark, patched silently. · f=kit imagery section flag kit gap atlas/operator; interim templates labeled provisional., generation capability deployment templates still valuable: they parameterize briefs human designers external tools. · b:with Other Skills=**atlas's kit** defines direction (and owns amendments); skill operationalizes generation. kit's AI-imagery policy governs whether skill runs all., `content-image` (sibling) supplies model-agnostic prompt craft; skill supplies brand-specific constants fill it., `asset-pipeline` (sibling) consumer, run., **Multi-brand operators:** one file brand; style bleed between brands atlas's multi-brand-system territory.